Alembic migrations for the simulator.

This directory holds the PostGIS schema migrations. The
``CREATE EXTENSION postgis`` bootstrap migration is the first migration
in ``versions/``; it must run idempotently and is a prerequisite for
every later migration.

Generate a revision (autogenerate after model changes):

    alembic revision -m "add <table>" --autogenerate

Apply migrations:

    alembic upgrade head

Roll back to base:

    alembic downgrade base

Configuration notes:
- alembic.ini ships with an empty sqlalchemy.url; env.py injects the URL
  from Settings.DATABASE_URL at runtime so a single source of truth is
  preserved between the FastAPI app and migration tooling.
- target_metadata is bound to src.db.base.Base.metadata. env.py imports
  src.db.models so autogenerate can compare model state to the live DB.
